snippet.title: Lesson 20 - Integration Style:  Shared Database
snippet.description: In this lesson Mark Richards continues talking about integration styles by discussing the shared database integration style. The shared database integration style is a common way to integrate systems, but carries with it some negatives and implications you should be aware of before choosing this integration style. Stay tuned each Monday for more lessons in Software Architecture at https://www.developertoarchitect.com/lessons/.
